<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="597" type="key">
<keyStep pageId="8" pageNumber="597">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,285,660]" box="[151,1437,285,307]" pageId="8" pageNumber="597">
<keyLead box="[151,1437,285,307]" pageId="8" pageNumber="597">1 Telson terminating in elongate distally rounded spatulate endpiece laterally armed with spines.........................2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,285,660]" box="[151,1436,315,337]" pageId="8" pageNumber="597">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,315,337]" pageId="8" pageNumber="597">- Telson truncate distally................................................................................ 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="8" pageNumber="597">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,285,660]" pageId="8" pageNumber="597">
<keyLead pageId="8" pageNumber="597">
2. Carapace corrugated dorsally in gastric region; ocular peduncle short, nearly as long as broad at base; cornea reduced, and unpigmented...................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Wasmer, 2022" authorityName="Wasmer" authorityYear="2022" box="[1185,1379,373,394]" class="Malacostraca" family="Oplophoridae" genus="Hymenodora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="597" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chacei" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[1185,1379,373,394]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="597">Hymenodora chacei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1385,1437,374,395]" pageId="8" pageNumber="597" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,285,660]" pageId="8" pageNumber="597">
<keyLead pageId="8" pageNumber="597">
- Carapace not corrugated in gastric region; ocular peduncle about twice as long as broad at base; cornea faceted and pigmented......................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Wasmer, 1972" authorityName="Wasmer" authorityYear="1972" box="[1017,1436,432,454]" class="Malacostraca" family="Oplophoridae" genus="Hymenodora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="597" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acanthitelsonis">
<emphasis box="[1017,1293,432,453]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="597">Hymenodora acanthitelsonis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Wasmer, R. A." box="[1299,1436,432,454]" pageId="8" pageNumber="597" pagination="87 - 91" refId="ref6020" refString="Wasmer, R. A. (1972) A new species of Hymenodora (Decapoda, Oplophoridae) from the Northwestern Pacific. Crustaceana, 22 (1), 87 - 91. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 156854072 X 00705" type="journal article" year="1972">Wasmer, 1972</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="8" pageNumber="597">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,285,660]" box="[151,1436,461,483]" pageId="8" pageNumber="597">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,461,483]" pageId="8" pageNumber="597">3. Rostrum short, reaching little beyond cornea of eye.......................................................... 4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,285,660]" box="[151,1436,491,513]" pageId="8" pageNumber="597">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,491,513]" pageId="8" pageNumber="597">
- Rostrum longer, reaching at least as far as distal end of antennular peduncle......... 
<taxonomicName authority="Rathbun, 1902" authorityName="Rathbun" authorityYear="1902" box="[1077,1436,491,513]" class="Malacostraca" family="Oplophoridae" genus="Hymenodora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="597" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="frontalis">
<emphasis box="[1077,1288,491,512]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="597">Hymenodora frontalis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Rathbun, M. J." box="[1295,1436,491,513]" pageId="8" pageNumber="597" pagination="885 - 905" refId="ref5558" refString="Rathbun, M. J. (1902) Descriptions of new decapod Crustaceans from the west coast of North America. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 24 (1272), 885 - 905. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.1272.885" type="journal article" year="1902">Rathbun, 1902</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="8" pageNumber="597">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,285,660]" pageId="8" pageNumber="597">
<keyLead pageId="8" pageNumber="597">
4. Second maxilliped with podobranch; upper border of rostrum more or less gently concave from above orbital margin, lower border not markedly convex; no crescent-shaped sulcus in hepatic region of carapace.... 
<taxonomicName authority=", Smith, 1886" authorityName=", Smith" authorityYear="1886" box="[1102,1436,549,571]" class="Malacostraca" family="Oplophoridae" genus="Hymenodora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="597" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis box="[1102,1307,549,570]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="597">Hymenodora gracilis</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, S. I." box="[1319,1436,549,571]" pageId="8" pageNumber="597" pagination="187 - 198" refId="ref5915" refString="Smith, S. I. (1886) The abyssal decapod Crustracea of the &quot; Albatross &quot; dredgings in the North Atlantic. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 5, 17, 187 - 198. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222938609460133" type="journal article" year="1886">Smith, 1886</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,285,660]" pageId="8" pageNumber="597">
<keyLead pageId="8" pageNumber="597">
- Second maxilliped without podobranch; superior border of rostrum generally descending from high swollen anterior part of carapace, inferior border often convex; crescent-shaped sulcus present in hepatic region of carapace........................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName authority="(Buchholz, 1874)" baseAuthorityName="Buchholz" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[1048,1436,637,660]" class="Malacostraca" family="Oplophoridae" genus="Hymenodora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="597" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glacialis">
<emphasis box="[1048,1263,637,658]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="597">Hymenodora glacialis</emphasis>
(Buchholz, 1874)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
